{
  "texts": [
    "Common kernels include linear, polynomial, Gaussian (RBF), and others.• Optimization Problem: SVM's primary goal is to maximize the margin while minimizing misclassification error.",
    "This objective is formulated as an optimization problem.",
    "The margin is mathematically expressed as the distance between the hyperplane and the closest support vectors.",
    "The aim is to balance classification accuracy with maximizing this margin.• Lagrange Multipliers and Dual Problem: SVM's optimization problem involves equality and inequality constraints.Lagrange multipliers convert this constrained problem into an unconstrained one.",
    "The dual problem solution involves finding optimal Lagrange multiplier values, which correspond to support vectors.• Kernel Trick in the Dual Problem: By employing the kernel trick, computations occur in the transformed space."
  ]
}